The paper focuses on exploring visual designs for summarizing and analyzing multi-class point data using binned aggregation. This involves designing effective visual representations of summaries of large collections of points, which is a common problem in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses various design decisions and guidelines for creating effective visualizations, which is relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and data management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper provides a web-based implementation for experimenting with design choices, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
